UML:TaggedValue.value:
This package contains the design inputs for the <<NewPhysicalArchModule>> . The <<NewPhysicalModule>> package is used to define the behaviors, specs, and architecture that is needed for the new module. The <<NewPhysicalArchModule>> Package provides the high level description for the module that needs to be incorporated into the detailed design. The package contains:
  1. Inputs Canvas
  2. Design Specs and Reqs Analysis
  3. Use Cases
  4. Design Analysis
  5. Test Cases

The Design and Analysis is the package contains the block diagrams that describe the module's needed parts. There are two views of this show, the Block Definition Diagram that shows the tree of parts that make up the module and the Internal Block Diagram that defines how the blocks will interact.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: <<New Physical Arch Module>> Design Spec and Reqs Analysis

UML:TaggedValue.value: The flow down from System to Subsystem to Design Specs is important to capture as the context for which the requirements were created should be considered when creating the design specs. The Design Spec and Requirements Analysis package is contains the requirements flow down for the <<NewPhysicalArchModule>>.

Use cases care created to describe the various uses of the module from the actors perspective. The Use Cases herein are specifically written to capture the behaviors of the <<NewPhysicalArchModule>> by capturing actor's goals. The use case process for <<NewPhysicalArchModule>> is recursively iterative decomposing use cases to break <<NewPhysicalArchModule>> into parts.
This canvas is created to show the key design attributes for <<NewPhysicalArchModule>> which need to be considered when actual components are selected.
<<New Physical Arch Module>> -Smart Req Analysis Diagram
The <<NewPhysicalArchModule>> Ports Table list the ports for interfacing with the <<NewPhysicalArchModule>> and a description of their needed function.
